    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-07T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-07T02:00:00-05:00" n="379"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9239: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-07T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 7, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 8—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>384. 1. According to estimate of the Military Attaché’s office, there are now
                    about 130,000 Chinese troops concentrated on the Paoting-Tsangchow “front”
                    including elements of the 29th Army at Chochow, 31,000 at Paoting, 43,000 in the
                    Tinghsien-Shihkiachwang area, 17,000 in the Shuntefu-Hantai region, 12,000 at
                    Tsangchow and 27,000 at Tehsien. Of these I am told 13 divisions totaling some
                    43,000 are <pb facs="0360" n="353" xml:id="pg_353"/> Central Government troops.
                    At Tsinan there are 8,000 soldiers, from Yangchikow to Chefoo 9,000, and
                    Weihsien to Tsingtao 8,000.</p>
                <p>2. General von Falkenhausen, Chief German Military Adviser, is reliably reported
                    to be now at Paoting.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department, Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
